#let hebbian_theory = link("https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Hebbian_theory&oldid=1352806978")[Hebbian Theory]

The phrase `Neurons that fire together, wire together` almost captures #hebbian_theory in an aphorism. It turns out rather that neurons that fire right after one another wire together; nonetheless, this characterizes associative learning quite well. 
